title: American Museum of Natural History
short_desc: The American Museum of Natural History is one of the largest museums in the world, with more than 32 million specimens including a 94 foot long blue whale, the largest meteorite on display in any museum worldwide, and a 563 carat star sapphire.
Desc1: The American Museum of Natural History is one of the largest museums in the world.  The museum complex consists of 45 permanent exhibition halls, as well as a planetarium and library.  The museum holds more than 32 million specimens of human, animal, plant, fossil, mineral, rock, meteorite, and human cultural artifacts.
Desc2: Must See: Scales of the Universe exhibit,  Hayden Planetarium, 94 foot long blue whale, giant sequoia, Barosaurus  and other dinosaur skeletons, 563 carat Star of India, Ahnighito meteorite (largest on display in any museum worldwide), and butterfly conservatory. (seasonal).
hours: Open daily. 10 AM-5:45 PM

title: BNL Science Learning Center
short_desc: " The Science Learning Center offers programs to students in grades 1-12, featuring interactive exhibits, hands-on labs, and programs that demonstrate basic scientific principles."  - from https://www.bnl.gov/education/
Desc1: " The Science Learning Center offers programs to students in grades 1-12, featuring interactive exhibits, hands-on labs, and programs that demonstrate basic scientific principles."  - from https://www.bnl.gov/education/
Desc2: Must See: The hands-on labs.
hours: Hours: by reservation

title: The Brooklyn Children's Museum
short_desc: The Brooklyn Children's Museum was the first museum in the United States to cater specifically to children
Desc1: "The Brooklyn Children's Museum was the first museum in the United States to cater specifically to children.  The museum offers interactive learning adventures through hands-on exhibitions, multicultural performances, creative workshops and an extensive collection of cultural artifacts and natural science specimens."
Desc2: Must See: The Water Lab and the blue sand pit.
hours: Open Tuesday - Sunday 10 AM - 5 PM

title: Buffalo Museum of Science
short_desc: The museum contains more than 700,000 specimens, most of which pertain to the Greater Niagara region, and cover areas such as anthropology, botany, entomology, mycology, paleontology, and zoology.
Desc1: "Since 2010, the BMS has been on an aggressive path to renovate all of the museum's permanent exhibit experiences, transforming its former diorama-based exhibits into eight highly interactive and immersive science studio exhibit spaces...The museum has also added the Explorations early childhood gallery to its permanent offerings, as well as the National Geographic 3D Cinema presented by M&T Bank...A significant part of the Museum's collection of over 700,000 specimens pertain to the Greater Niagara Region and form by far the most complete record of life in all of its forms in this area in anthropology, botany, entomology, mycology, paleontology and zoology." - from http://www.sciencebuff.org/site/aboutus
Desc2: Must See: The rooftop observatory (opening in 2016) and Seymour the Mastodon and Stanley the Albertosaurus.
hours: Open daily. 10 AM-4:00 PM

title: The Children's Museum of Science and Technology
short_desc: The Children's Museum includes interactive exhibits covering a range of areas such as construction, maker spaces, and nano-scale exploration.
Desc1: All exhibits at the Children's Museum are designed with science discovery and play in mind.  Exhibits include the Construction Junction, Maker Space, Move It / Shake It, Nature Place, and Nano Exploration.
Desc2: Must See: The Magnetic Ball Wall, planetarium, and the Skyline Tool Box
hours: Open Wednesday from 1 PM - 5 PM and Thursday -Sunday 10 AM - 5 PM

title: Hudson River Museum
short_desc: The museum contains an extensive collection of art works from the Hudson River school, and also features exhibits on the history, science, and heritage of the region.  Also featured are the Andrus Planetarium and the Glenview Mansion.
Desc1: Founded in 1919 as Yonkers Museum, the facility the largest museum in Westchester County.  The museum contains an extensive collection of art works from the Hudson River school, and also features exhibits on the history, science, and heritage of the region.  The museum is now home to the only public planetarium in Westchester County.  Central to its history is the Glenview Mansion, a house built in 1877, which contains six period rooms.
Desc2: Must See: The Andrus Planetarium and the Glenview Mansion period rooms.
hours: Open Wednesday - Sunday 12 PM - 5 PM

title: Intrepid Sea, Air & Space Museum
short_desc: The Intrepid Sea, Air & Space Museum is dedicated to the exhibition and interpretation of history, science and service related to the aircraft carrier?Intrepid.
Desc1: "The Intrepid Sea, Air & Space Museum is dedicated to the exhibition and interpretation of history, science and service as related to its home aboard the aircraft carrier Intrepid, a National Historic Landmark. As you explore the Museum you will be able to examine original artifacts, view historic video footage and explore interactive exhibits." - from http://www.intrepidmuseum.org/The-Intrepid-Experience/Exhibits.aspx
Desc2: Must See: The Enterprise space shuttle, Growler (the only American guided missile submarine open to the public), and Concorde plane.
hours: Open Monday - Friday 10 AM - 5 PM, and Saturday, Sunday, and Holidays 10 AM - 6 PM (Spring / Summer Hours); Open daily 10 AM - 5 PM (Fall/ Winter Hours)

title: Kopernik Observatory & Science Center
short_desc: The Kopernik Observatory and Science Center's mission is to offer hands-on investigations and outreach programs for educating all ages about astronomy and science
Desc1: "The Kopernik Observatory and Science Center's mission is to offer hands-on investigations and outreach programs for educating all ages about astronomy and science using advanced optical telescopes, computers and other tools. It is the first science laboratory facility in New York State designed for K-12 teachers, students and their families and has been one of the best-sited and best equipped public observatories in the Northeast United States for nearly the last 40 years." - from http://www.kopernik.org/visitor-info/about-kopernik/
Desc2: Must See: The observatory telescopes and the adults-only Moonlight Caf?
hours: Open Fridays from 7:30 PM (March - November); only on special weekend nights once a month from 6:30 PM (December - February); Daily Free Tours on weekdays from 10 AM - 2 PM (by appointment)

title: Long Island Children's Museum
short_desc: The Long Island Children?s Museum is home to 14 hands-on, interactive exhibit galleries, a 145-seat state-of-the-art theater and three classroom-size learning studios.
Desc1: "The Long Island Children?s Museum today is home to 14 hands-on, interactive exhibit galleries, a 145-seat state-of-the-art theater and three classroom-size learning studios." - from http://www.licm.org/backgrounder.php
Desc2: Must See: Climb-It (two-story climbing structure), and giant bubbles exhibit; TotSpot for youngest visitors
hours: Open daily from 10 AM - 5 PM (June 30 - August 30); Open Tuesday - Sunday from 10 AM - 5 PM (September- June)

title: Long Island Museum of Science and Technology
short_desc: The museum's main goal is to excite and enrich young people, many of whom will be inspired to fill the 21st Century need for a technologically skilled workforce.
Desc1: " Long Island's "hands-on" science and technology center is designed to expand to major proportions and world-class quality. Its main goal is to excite and enrich young people, many of whom will be inspired to fill the 21st Century need for a technologically skilled workforce." - from http://techisland.org/museum.asp
Desc2: Must See: The bed of nails.
hours: Hours Unknown

title: Cradle of Aviation Museum
short_desc: Explore over 150,000 square feet featuring 75 air and spacecraft from a hot air balloon to an actual Apollo Lunar Module and learn about why Long Island is called the Cradle of Aviation.
Desc1: "Explore over 150,000 square feet featuring 75 air and spacecraft from a hot air balloon to an actual Apollo Lunar Module and learn about Long Island's role and why we are called the Cradle of Aviation. Our eight exhibit galleries are in chronological order and throughout the museum our volunteer docents are there to share their aerospace experience. There are over 30 hands-on exhibits, a half dozen cockpits to climb into and many short films through-out the exhibits." - from http://www.cradleofaviation.org/plan_your_visit/galleries.html
Desc2: Must See: Charles Lindbergh's first plane (Jn-4 Jenny), Spitit of St. Louis, and the Jet Blue Sky Theater Planetarium. Also the Junior Jet Club for smaller visitors.
hours: Open Tuesday - Sunday 9:30 PM - 5:00 PM ; Open Mondays that fall on holidays and school breaks.

title: Long Island Science Center
short_desc: A 'learning by doing philosophy' underpins the Science Center's programs and exhibits; come explore more than 30 hands-on exhibits.
Desc1: The mission of the Long Island Science Center is to promote the knowledge and love of Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics. Explore more than 30 hands-on exhibits in the Center. "This 'learning by doing philosophy' underpins the Science Center's programs and exhibits.  As people freely explore the materials and activities available, they become empowered and motivated to learn more about Science and life." - from http://www.lisciencecenter.org/ABOUTUS.aspx
Desc2: Must See: 30 hands-on exhibits
hours: Open Saturdays 11 AM - 4 PM (September - June); Open 11 AM - 4 PM Tuesday - Saturday (July and August)

title: Mid-Hudson Children's Museum
short_desc: The Mid-Hudson Children's Museum is the ideal destination for families with children ages 0-6, offering exhibits that get kids moving, exploring, building, pretending, collaborating, creating and discovering.
Desc1: "The Mid-Hudson Children's Museum is the ideal destination for families with children ages 0-6. We celebrate childhood and are proud to offer exhibits that get kids moving, exploring, building, pretending, collaborating, creating and discovering. Our exhibits focus on nature, science, literacy, art, music and community and allow children the opportunity to develop foundational learning skills." - from http://www.mhcm.org/web/play/home
Desc2: Must See: The Wonder Dome (sensory exhibit exploring light and color) and the Imagination Playground.
hours: Open Tuesday - Saturday 9:30 AM - 5 PM; Sunday 11 AM - 5 PM

title: Milton J. Rubenstein Museum of Science & Technology (AKA: The Discovery Center)
short_desc: Explore the human body, fossils and space in this kid-oriented learning center.
Desc1: Kid-oriented  center with a domed IMAX theater explores the human body, fossils & space.  Permanent exhibits include: Earth Science Discovery Cave, Life Sciences, the Lockheed Martin Flight & Space exhibit, Science Playhouse and Technotown.
Desc2: Must See: Giant replicas of the human haeart and brain, fossil pit, and Coral Reef Adventure Tank, Science Playhouse (climbing maze), Silverman Planetarium, and giant kinetic sculpture.
hours: Open Wednesday - Sunday 10 AM - 5 PM; also open Mondays and Tuesdays during holidays / school vacations, and Tuesdays in the summer

title: Museum of Mathematics

title: Museum of the Earth at the Paleontological Research Institution
short_desc: Explore Earth's prehistoric past through fossils, science-inspired art, and engaging displays.  Watch paleontologists uncover fossils and dinosaur bones?
Desc1:
"Explore Earth and its prehistoric past?from the tiniest trilobite to the mighty mastodon? through engaging displays, hands-on features, stunning fossils, and science-inspired art...Watch paleontologists uncover dinosaur bones and other exciting fossils in Prep Lab.
Journey 540 million years back in time with the 500-foot mural Rock of Ages, Sands of Time." - from http://www.priweb.org/planyourvisit.php
Desc2: Must See: The fossil lab (take home your own fossils), Hyde Park Mastodon (one of the most complete mastodon skeletons ever found), and the 44 food Right Whale.
hours: Open Monday - Saturday 10 AM - 5 PM; Sunday 11 AM - 5 PM (Summer Hours).  Monday 10 AM - 5 PM; Closed Tuesday - Wednesday; Thursday - Saturday 10 AM - 5 PM; Sunday 11 AM - 5 PM (Winter Hours).

Desc2: Must See:

title: Natural History Museum of the Adirondacks, The WILD Center
short_desc: This 54,000 square foot center is dedicated to helping visitors understand the Adirondacks region, and includes exhibit halls, animal encounters, live shows, and the opportunity to take a woodland showshoe to the Raquette River.
Desc1: "There's a day's worth of things to see and do at the 54,000-square-foot Center and on our 81-acre campus. Come explore the exhibit halls, create your own work of art, meet one of our many animals at an animal encounter, take a woodland snowshoe down to the Raquette River, join us for a live show, or watch one of many amazing films produced by The Wild Center. " - from http://www.wildcenter.org/
Desc2: Must See: The "Moments, Reimagining Nature through Art" exhibit (create your own art) and the "Wild Walk" (coming in 2015)
hours: Open Memorial Day-Labor Day, 10 AM-6 PM; Labor Day - Columbus Day, 10 AM-5 PM; closed month of April; Friday, Saturday, and Sunday 1 PM - 5 PM until Memorial Day

title: New York State Museum
short_desc: The nation's oldest and largest state museum includes exhibits tracing New York's natural and cultural past including 9/11 artifacts and a 1890s carousel.
Desc1: The nation's oldest and largest state museum, the museum houses art, artifacts (prehistoric and historic), and ecofacts that reflect New York?s cultural, natural, and geological development.  Permanent exhibits include fossils from the area, birds of New York, Harlem in the 20's, minerals of New York, and others.
Desc2: Must See: An 1890's carousel, the Cohoes Mastodon skeleton, and fire fighting vehicles from the 19th and 20th centuries.
hours: Open Tuesday - Sunday 9:30 AM - 5 PM; Closed Mondays.

title: New York Transit Museum
Desc2: Must See:

title: Niagara Science Museum
short_desc: "We are proud to be able to present our artifacts-antique science instruments and philosophical apparatus-in recreated 'old fashion' functional laboratories."  The museum covers science from 1870-1930.
Desc1: "The Niagara Science Museum (NSM) is a sanctuary for the preservation and appreciation of old science instruments and philosophical apparatus."  - from http://www.niagarasciencemuseum.org/aboutus.htm
Desc2: Must See: The Discharge in Gases Laboratory (watch sparks jump) and other live demonstrations (instruments are fully functioning)
hours: Open Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday, and Sunday from 12 - 2 PM (June 1st - October 15th); by appointment only during September and October.

title: Sciencenter
short_desc: The museum offers guests of all ages more than 250 exhibits, educational programs, a gift shop, and seasonal outdoor science playground and mini-golf course.
Desc1: "The Sciencenter inspires excitement for science through interactive exhibits and programs that engage, educate and empower. Our non-profit, hands-on museum offers guests of all ages more than 250 exhibits, educational programs, a gift shop, and seasonal outdoor science playground and mini-golf course." - from http://www.sciencenter.org/plan-your-visit.html
Desc2: Must See: A thermal image of yourself on a 50" screen in the Mars and Stars Exhibit, the mini golf course, the world?s only Kevlar cable suspension bridge (Science Playground), and the Sagan Planet Walk . For the littlest ones, visit Curiosity Corner (water table, infant area, and more).
hours: Open Tuesday - Saturday 10 AM - 5 PM; Sunday 12 PM - 5 PM; closed Monday

title: Sony Wonder Technology Lab
short_desc: The Sony Wonder Technology Lab (SWTL) is a FREE four-story, interactive technology and entertainment museum for all ages.
Desc1: "The Sony Wonder Technology Lab (SWTL) is a FREE four-story, interactive technology and entertainment museum for all ages...Through its permanent exhibits and innovative programs, including Sci-Tech workshops, ongoing screenings and associations with well-respected local non-profit and educational institutions, SWTL aims to educate and cultivate the next generation of leaders in media, science, technology and the arts." - from http://www.sonywondertechlab.com/admission
Desc2: Must See: the Sensi-Tile exhibit, Shadow Garden and Sand Interactive, Music Mixer (collaborate on a music track), and Moviemaker (create your own trailer). Also worth seeing the Dance Motion Capture, WSWL Production Studio, Animation Studio, and GameBuilder exhibits.
hours: Open Tuesday - Saturday 9:30 AM - 5 PM; closed Sunday, Monday, and major holidays (reservations required)

title: Staten Island Children's Museum
short_desc: The Staten Island Children?s Museum offers 40,000 square feet of interactive exhibits as well as a 4-acre East Meadow, and a picnic and performance pavilion.
Desc1: Founded in 1974 and located in a historical setting on the grounds of Snug Harbor Cultural Center & Botanical Gardens, the Staten Island Children?s Museum offers 40,000 square feet of interactive exhibits as well as a 4-acre East Meadow, and a picnic and performance pavilion.
Desc2: Must See: The human-sized ant hill, Big Games exhibit (life-sized chess, giant dominoes, etc.), and the Sea of Boats (outdoor, sea-faring, soft surface play area).
hours: Open Tuesday - Friday 12 PM - 5 PM (school year) and 10 AM - 5 PM (summer and school holidays); Saturday and Sunday 10 AM - 5 PM; closed most Mondays

title: Staten Island Institute of Arts and Sciences (Staten Island Museum)
short_desc: Founded in 1881 by fourteen of New York City?s first environmental activists, the Staten Island Museum houses artifacts and specimens from ancient to contemporary periods.  Holdings are organized into three main collections: Natural Sciences, Fine Art, and History Archives and Library.
Desc1: Founded in 1881 by fourteen of New York City?s first environmental activists, the Staten Island Museum is the place for exploring the dynamic connection between natural science, art and history since 1881.  The museum's holdings are organized into three main collections: Natural Sciences, Fine Art, and Historical Archives and Library.  " The natural science collections encompass over 500,000 botanical, biological, anthropological and mineral specimens including bird nests and eggs, mounted animals, fossils, shells, and a significant collection of insects, including important type of specimens. Based upon a 19th-century model, the art collection includes works spanning prehistory to the modern period, with representations of diverse world cultures from both the Western and Non-Western traditions. The historical collections include a library, maps and atlases, early films, audio recordings, photographs, historical objects, ephemera and archival documents reaching back to the 17th century." - from http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Staten_Island_Museum
Desc2: Must See: The entomology collection (comprising more than 500,000 specimens) and the "Return of the 17-year Cicadas" exhibit.
hours: Open Monday - Friday 11 AM - 5 PM; Saturday 10 AM - 5 PM ; Sunday 12 PM - 5 PM

title: Trolley Museum of New York
short_desc: The museum shares the rich history of rail transportation and the role it played in the Hud?son Valley region through displays of trolley, subway and rapid transit cars from the United States and Europe.
Desc1: "The goals of the museum are to offer a ride to the public and through exhibits and educational programs to share the rich history of rail transportation and the role it played in the Hud?son Valley region.  In addition to static displays of trolley, subway and rapid transit cars from the United States and Europe, an excursion ride runs 1? miles from the foot of Broad?way in downtown Kingston to picnic grounds on the shore of the Hudson River at Kingston Point. " - http://www.tmny.org/tmnyinfo.html
Desc2: Must See: Trolley ride to the Hudson salt marshes.  Don't miss the insides of the trolleys on exhibit.
hours: Open weekends and holidays 12 PM to 5 PM (May 9 - October 12)

title: Wings of Eagles Discovery Center
short_desc: Wings of Eagles Discovery Center has an wide range of aircraft, replicas, missiles, flight simulators and other items on display for public viewing.
Desc1: Wings of Eagles Discovery Center has an wide range of aircraft, replicas, missiles, flight simulators and other items on display for public viewing.  The museum has an extensive collection of aircraft on display for public viewing. Most were originally used in military settings for either training or combat purposes ranging from World War II to the present.
Desc2: Must See: The flight simulators, 18 aircrafts on display, and the General Electric GAU-8A ?Avenger? 30mm Revolving Cannon.
hours: Open Tuesday - Friday 11 AM - 3 PM; Saturday 11 AM - 4 PM (Spring Hours)
